node.text: It’s not the emotions that often cause the problem or profiling suffering. It’s how we respond to the uncomfortable emotions, whether that be by trying to suppress and avoid, indulge in assumptions, or harshly judge the feelings. When you choose to honor your feelings by giving them space and trying to find out why they exist, you will move through them quicker and the results will be more sustainable.

This is so hard especially for parents, caretakers, and those who’s trauma response is to be the fixer. I know I struggle with this a lot! But often then best way to be supportive is to be present with someone but not take on their load, otherwise you’ll burn out and they won’t grow. 

For more mental health tips and strategies sign up for my free weekly newsletters drleaf.com!
